
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Conan Fitness System

class Person {
  +firstName: String
  +familyName: String
  +birthDate: Date
}

class Trainer {
  +diploma: String
}

class Member {
  +memberId: Integer
}

class Center {
  +name: String
  +address: String
  +rooms: List<Room>
}

class Room {
  +roomNumber: Integer
  +maxCapacity: Integer
}

class Session {
  +date: Date
  +startTime: Time
  +type: String
  +center: Center
  +room: Room
  +trainer: Trainer
}

class GroupSession {
  +session: Session
}

class IndividualSession {
  +session: Session
}

class Participant {
  +person: Person
  +session: Session
}

class SupervisedSession {
  +trainer: Trainer
  +session: Session
}

' Associations and Inheritance

Person <|-- Trainer
Person <|-- Member
Center "1" *-- "0..*" Room
Session <|-- GroupSession
Session <|-- IndividualSession
Person "0..*" *-- "0..*" Participant
Participant "0..*" *-- "1" Session
Trainer "0..*" *-- "0..*" SupervisedSession
SupervisedSession "0..*" *-- "1" Session

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Person`**: Base class with `firstName`, `familyName`, and `birthDate`. This represents all people, including members, trainers, and prospects.
- **`Trainer`** and **`Member`**: Subclasses of `Person`. A `Trainer` has a `diploma`, while `Member` could have an ID or other attributes if needed (you can extend this).
- **`Center`**: Represents each fitness center. Has a name, address, and list of rooms.
- **`Room`**: Belongs to a center and has a room number and maximum capacity.
- **`Session`**: Abstract class representing either a group or individual session. Stores date, time, center, and room.
- **`GroupSession`** and **`IndividualSession`**: Subclasses of `Session`. Group sessions require a trainer.
- **`Participant`**: Links a person to a session. Used to record which people participated in which sessions.
- **`SupervisedSession`**: Links a trainer to a session (only for group sessions).

This model allows:
- Recording of participation for members (including those who haven't joined any session yet).
- Tracking of trainers and their supervision of group sessions (including those who haven’t supervised any session yet).
- Managing centers, rooms, and session scheduling according to the constraints.

